Balhae is a historical heritage belonging to many countries. Korean user Koraskadi always deletes references from other countries. Imagine balhae belongs to them only in Korea.
The Manchus clearly believe that Balhae is his ancestor. Just as Koreans consider themselves to be descendants of the Jin State, Manchu is needed.
The description of Goguryeo as one of the three Korean countries has not been eliminated. The arbitrary removal of different translations violates the spirit of Wikipedia.

According to the contents of the reference materials, the most used words in the English media are “Balhae” followed by “Bohai”, which is the direct spelling of “渤海”, and “Palhae” is obviously the Romanization of Korean, the reference material can prove Scholars from other countries basically do not use it. Regarding the language problem of Бохай, Russian historical attitude towards Bohai is neutral, and there are many research results. Many evidences point to the Tungusic language. Th
Whether Balhae is a descendant of Goguryeo is controversial，References indicate that Balhae is likely to be mohe，This is recognized except for Koreans.
